highlights.text: “Mr. Brightside” by The Killers has been on Top Songs Australia the longest, at 458 weeks straight.
“TIT FOR TAT” by Tate McRae is the highest new entry on Top Songs Australia at #4.
Olivia Dean has the most spots on Top Songs Australia. “Man I Need” is the highest at #1.
“A COLD PLAY” by The Kid LAROI is the biggest gainer on Top Songs Australia, up 59 spots at #82.
